<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Eichhornia</i> <i>crassipes</i>, <i>Ludwigia</i> <i>hexapetala</i>, <i>Ludwigia</i> <i>peploides</i> ssp. <i>montevidensis</i> or other <i>Ludwigia</I> species are dominant as emergent or floating plants on the water surface.<i>Azolla</i> <i>filiculoides</i> </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 3 m; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Permanently and seasonally flooded freshwater habitats with still water or on ground surfaces after water levels have dropped. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Ludwigia peploides</i> ssp. <i>montevidensis, L. palustris,</i> and <i>L. repens</i> as OBL plants. </div>
</div>

		
